- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses techniques for controlling energy consumption in residential settings to manage demand on the power grid, which falls under the domain of systems and control.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper discusses real-time scheduling of household appliances to optimize energy consumption, which could involve the use of AI techniques such as machine learning or optimization algorithms.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): As mentioned above, the paper could involve the use of machine learning techniques to optimize energy consumption scheduling.
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper discusses the economics of energy consumption scheduling and reducing peak load demand, which could fall under the domain of computational finance or engineering.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper may discuss the development of software or algorithms for controlling energy consumption in residential settings.
